 to define predicates in exactly the same way as lambda expressions can be used to define functions.<p />Higher-order properties of Scheme are preserved; predicates can be passed to and returned from function applications. Predicate applications can appear as terms in functions. On the other hand, function applications can appear as terms in predicates, and can be formal as well as actual arguments, but only as long as they can be evaluated according to the usual Scheme semantics prohibiting access to unbound variables (except for constructor applications).</p><p><u>Bibtex citation:</u></p><pre>@article{
   key = "Oz:entry140"
   author = "Pierre Bonzon"
   title = "A Metacircular Evaluator for a Logical Extension of Scheme"
   journal = "Lisp and Symbolic Computation: An International Journal"
   publisher = "Kluwer Academic Publishers"
   volume = "3"
   number = "2"
   pages = "113-133"
   month = "March"
   year = "1990"
}
</pre></td></tr></table></body></html>